TI  - State Government Promotion of Manufacturing Exports: A Gap Analysis
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 637
EP  - 658
VL  - 23
IS  - 4
AB  - This study empirically examines the level of the export-related expertise of manufacturing firms in a Midwestern state of the United States, various problems they face in export business, and types of government assistance desired, by their stage of export involvement. It also investigates the appropriateness of government export assistance and the gap between governmental export promotion efforts and private sector needs. It is shown that the identification of expertise, problems, and government assistance needs by export stage can help government agencies develop a systematic approach to export promotion.
